{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2022-1578","published":"2022-03-19T11:03:38Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:17:52.524303Z","upstream":["CVE-2022-0711"],"summary":"haproxy security update","details":"HAProxy is a free, very fast and reliable solution offering high availability, load balancing, and proxying for TCP and HTTP-based applications. It is particularly suited for very high traffic web sites and powers quite a number of the world's most visited ones.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA flaw was found in the way HAProxy processed HTTP responses containing the &quot;Set-Cookie2&quot; header. This flaw could allow an attacker to send crafted HTTP response packets which lead to an infinite loop, eventually resulting in a denial of service condition. The highest threat from this vulnerability is availability.(CVE-2022-0711)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"haproxy","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/haproxy&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"2.2.16-3.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["haproxy-debuginfo-2.2.16-3.oe1.aarch64.rpm","haproxy-debugsource-2.2.16-3.oe1.aarch64.rpm","haproxy-2.2.16-3.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["haproxy-help-2.2.16-3.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["haproxy-2.2.16-3.oe1.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["haproxy-2.2.16-3.oe1.x86_64.rpm","haproxy-debuginfo-2.2.16-3.oe1.x86_64.rpm","haproxy-debugsource-2.2.16-3.oe1.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2022-1578.json"}},{"package":{"name":"haproxy","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/haproxy&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"2.2.16-3.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["haproxy-debuginfo-2.2.16-3.oe1.aarch64.rpm","haproxy-debugsource-2.2.16-3.oe1.aarch64.rpm","haproxy-2.2.16-3.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["haproxy-help-2.2.16-3.oe1.noarch.rpm"],"src":["hapr